>>>>>>> # ISO Standard for Blood Glucose Monitoring Revised
>>>>>>> The International Organization for Standards (ISO) have made revisions
to the ISO 15197 Standard for blood glucose monitoring. The revised standard
will come into effect in May, rendering some meter systems as non-compliant.
>>>>>>> These changes are expected to affect up to a third of people diagnosed
with diabetes. It is crucial that healthcare professionals take urgent action
as test strips will become unavailable for non-compliant meter systems.
Healthcare professionals must check and upgrade their patients’ blood glucose
meter systems for compliance ahead of the implementation of ISO Standard
>>>>>>> Simon O’Neill, Director of Health Intelligence and Professional
Liaison at Diabetes UK, said: “It’s important that people have continuous
access to testing so they can ensure their diabetes is well controlled.
>>>>>>> “We recommend healthcare professionals make their patients aware of
the changes and put procedures in place to make sure they are using a
compliant monitor so they won’t have any problems accessing strips when they
>>>>>>> BIVDA has producedguidancefor healthcare professionals which outlines
some of the changes to the revised ISO 15197 Standard and how to check if a
